-- Acron Says It Has Sold Exploration Permit for Potassium Salts in Canada
-- B y   A m a n d a   J o r d a n
-- 2010-10-18T11:13:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/acron-says-it-has-sold-exploration-permit-for-potassium-salts-in-canada.html
 OAO Acron, Russia’s third-largest
nitrogen fertilizer producer, sold the right to explore for
potassium salts at Canada’s KP 385 permit area in Saskatchewan
for C$6 million ($5.88 million).   To contact the reporter on this story:
